t uses Apple&#39;s A15 Bionic chip instead of the more powerful M1, but the former is still plenty quick for most needs. The big downside, as with most non-Pro iPads, is that it only has 64GB of storage by default. For more space, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlHOUxQTkxHP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTFvaC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZmEyYmU4NTEtNmIzMy00NDQ1LWEyNjgtMDc1ZGM4ZWM2MjU2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAWf4J9BTUx0wTz_deFyl1Ou2xPbLkKzetEgmuvzsmM2x&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09G9LPNLG" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09G9LPNLG?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">256GB variant</a> is on sale for a new low of $529.</p><h2> Apple iPad Pro 12.9-inch </h2><p><core-commerce id="232e0ba518a1484584368e7ebace3358" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJKTEYyQlJNP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTFvaC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZmEyYmU4NTEtNmIzMy00NDQ1LWEyNjgtMDc1ZGM4ZWM2MjU2In0&amp;signature=AQAAASLW1LRub4aYU5TnR5WighaHeqAmm_QrjDV796ulfjGZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BJLF2BRM" class="rapid-with-clickid">12.9-inch iPad Pro</a> , meanwhile, is down to $1,049. That&#39;s $50 <strong>&nbsp;</strong> off A