gaming-180033983.html">gaming-friendly features</a> like <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/variablerefreshrate">VRR</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/autolowlatencymode">ALLM</a> , and it comes in a wider range of sizes than the S95B. It works with all the major HDR formats, too, Dolby Vision included. It&#39;s just less ideal in a brightly-lit room.</p><p> LG has rolled out a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJWWEY3MkhWLz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby0xOGEtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIzNzhjYzIyLTIxOGQtNDZiMC1iMDkxLTgwOWQ5ZDg2NDc2ZiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQ1-utsrmfGz8DzugBTdMXMDjKTF_k6B3Q2hru6vc2Vq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BVXF72HV%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">new C3 model</a> for 2023, but it&#39;s pricier, and <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.cnet.com/tech/home-entertainment/lg-oled-c3-review-sets-the-standard-for-high-end-television-picture-quality/">many</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/features/lg-c3-vs-lg-c2">reviews</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/tools/compare/lg-c2-oled-vs-lg-c3-oled/31229/37848?usage=1&amp;threshold=0.10">suggest</a> it&#39;s only a marginal upgrade outside of adding support for DTS audio.</p><h2> Sony A80K </h2><p><core-commerce id="7b54f7cc0bdb4e428946860051e88366" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If the LG C2 goes out of stock, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSOTNUV1RRP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAUqWxdV4Pxgt0ttR0LKq3v6frPIXjO-0FbFHlD5dpQM6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09R93TWTQ" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sony A80K</a> is another commendable OLED TV. It&#39;s down to $1,098 for a 55-inch model and $1,498 for a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlSOUpQU1RIP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE4YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjM3OGNjMjItMjE4ZC00NmIwLWIwOTEtODA5ZDlkODY0NzZmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAT9KF3bTwtJzD66M8nqofeciUsJP-RIB3kIHG8RJ8ku6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09R9JPSTH" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09R9JPSTH?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">65-inch model</a> . Both deals mark new lows: The former is about $250 off its recent street price, while the latter is a roughly $300 discount. The C2 is broadly considered a better option thanks to its <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/tools/compare/sony-a80k-oled-vs-lg-c2-oled/31219/31229?usage=1&amp;threshold=0.10">superior brightness</a> levels and two extra HDMI 2.1 ports, but the A80K still gets you the core benefits of an OLED display. It also runs on Google TV, which some may prefer to LG&#39;s webOS platform. Like the C2, you&#39;ll get the most out of it if you stay away from glare.</p><p> Sony&#39;s 2023 follow-up, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQ744hs0zUtdrLeGbAd2hpqEBUkKY1dqum-EeNwXbhy5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-OLED-inch-BRAVIA-Ultra%2Fdp%2FB0BYPVKW72" class="rapid-with-clickid">the A80L</a> , should be a better buy when prices come down, but right now it starts at $1,698. At that price, most should be better off with the Samsung S95B.</p><h2> LG B2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="0f41232957e14500af55d3fe3c17416a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you want a decent OLED TV for as little as possible, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATvpPBwnm1qG7Gs-jZVX_yPuX9AQrY9JkXpUrdHX8iSJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLG-55-Inch-Refresh-AI-Powered-OLED55B2PUA%2Fdp%2FB09RMND29B" class="rapid-with-clickid">55-inch LG B2</a> is a solid value at $897, which is a new low and a little over $100 off its typical street price. Again, this TV isn&#39;t as bright or color-rich as the C2 with HDR content, and it&#39;s limited to two HDMI 2.1 ports. It also runs on a slower processor. Still, the contrast and motion performance here will be a noticeable upgrade if you&#39;re coming from a more basic LCD TV and want to stay under $1,000. The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-li