uded, while others are sold with a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:34;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAW6bIUqHB2ldP4IjbBhBlxE7I2w88jfukKvngbg58cAy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Fthe-frame%2Fdigital-art-store%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">subscription</a> . The Frame&#39;s QLED panel lacks local dimming, so its contrast and HDR performance can&#39;t really compete with the best options in its price range. It only has one HDMI 2.1 port, too. But the image is still far from poor, and its design does well to blend into a wall, as <a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-the-frame-tv-irl-153546368.html">we&#39;ve professed before</a> .</p><h2> Hisense A6H </h2><p><core-commerce id="2d1f6b8c736d4551a4fb93406b0fcb11" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:36;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9IaXNlbnNlLTU1LUluY2gtVmlydHVhbC1DaHJvbWVjYXN0LTU1QTZIL2RwL0IwOVdRSlBXV1k_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMThhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMzc4Y2MyMi0yMThkLTQ2YjAtYjA5MS04MDlkOWQ4NjQ3NmYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAaaWO_bwhTpGujXbyqjCde7kmSzJclONdUqHb8DqIsF2&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHisense-55-Inch-Virtual-Chromecast-55A6H%2Fdp%2FB09WQJPWWY" class="rapid-with-clickid">Hisense A6H</a> is down to $228 for a <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:37;pos:1" href="http